{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"708fb4ef-bc77-4331-ba6b-a4e6de13f406","content":"To migrate your NUnit project to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)**:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (adds MTP support).\n   - Keep `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (still needed for compatibility).\n\n2. **Add the MTP package:**\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.NUnit\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP in your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **v5+** is required; v4.6.0 only supports VSTest.\n- No test code changes needed — `[Test]`, `[TestCase]`, etc. work as-is.\n- MTP runs tests as a standalone executable, so you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"975f4d7a-b96d-40a0-be35-cf3ad2dd7feb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge-based question - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"482D:237AB0:321917E:36A3F85:69FBE1CB"},"id":"a1a028ee-ab6b-46a6-a3c7-de2777504b72","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:50:38.905Z","parentId":"88468b48-7e8e-44be-aaf0-f9f87639189a"}
